SQLPlain English Select All<pre><code>SELECT * 
FROM Pupils;
</code></pre> <p>This will print out all the information in the database called Pupils using an astrix <code>*</code></p> <p></p> SQLPlain English Equals<pre><code>SELECT * 
FROM Pupils
WHERE House = 'Nevis';
</code></pre> <p>This will print out only the pupils who are in the guidance house Nevis from the Pupils table. Note there is speech marks around a string value.</p> <p></p> SQLPlain English Greater Than<pre><code>SELECT name, age 
FROM Pupils
WHERE age &gt; 15;
</code></pre> <p>This will print out only the attributes name and age from the Pupils table where the age is greater than or equal to 12.</p> <p></p> SQLPlain English Less Than<pre><code>SELECT name, age 
FROM Pupils
WHERE age &lt; 15;
</code></pre> <p>This will print out only the attributes name and age from the Pupils table where the age is greater than or equal to 12.</p> <p></p> SQLPlain English Greater Than or Equal too<pre><code>SELECT name, age 
FROM Pupils
WHERE age &gt;= 12;
</code></pre> <p>This will print out only the attributes name and age from the Pupils table where the age is greater than or equal to 12.</p> <p></p> SQLPlain English Less Than or Equal too<pre><code>SELECT name, age 
FROM Pupils
WHERE age &lt;= 15;
</code></pre> <p>This will print out only the attributes name and age from the Pupils table where the age is greater than or equal to 12.</p> <p></p> SQLPlain English AND<pre><code>SELECT * 
FROM Pupils
WHERE age &gt;= 12 AND age &lt;= 16;
</code></pre> <p>This will print out only the pupils who are aged greater than or equal to 16 and in guidance house Lochiel from the Pupils table.</p> <p></p> SQLPlain English OR<pre><code>SELECT * 
FROM Pupils
WHERE age &gt;= 12 OR age &lt;= 16;
</code></pre> <p>This will print out only the pupils who are aged greater than or equal to 16 and in guidance house Lochiel from the Pupils table.</p> <p></p> SQLPlain English Show Results in Ascending<pre><code>SELECT name, age, house 
FROM Pupils
WHERE age &lt; 15
ORDER BY age ASC;
</code></pre> <p>This will print out the attributes name, age and house from the pupils table that are less than 15 years old. The results will be sorted by the age attribute in ascending order.</p> <p></p> SQLPlain English Show Results in Descending Order<pre><code>SELECT name, age, house 
FROM Pupils
WHERE age &lt; 15
ORDER BY age DESC;
</code></pre> <p>This will print out the attributes name, age and house from the pupils table that are less than 15 years old. The results will be sorted by the age attribute in ascending order.</p>
